sentences: Sonny Emory (born December 23, 1962) is an American singer, songwriter, drummer and percussionist.
At first Emory played the drums on guitarist Bruce Hampton's 1984 album Arkansas and then upon keyboardist Joe Sample's 1987 LP Roles.

Emory also went on join the band Earth, Wind & Fire during 1987.
He later featured on saxophonist Brandon Fields 1988 album The Traveler.
Emory then featured alongside  Eric Clapton and David Sanborn on the soundtrack of the 1989 feature film Lethal Weapon 2.
